{
  "stem": "21308.4",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "They sent down the equipment to delouse everybody for typhus bugs.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And as I went around-- this was all on the first day-- we got an elementary system of feeding.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The food was all what you might call soup, and everybody had the same.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I mean, there was no particular kosher food for Jewish people or some other sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "No vegetarians.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "They-- they ate what was in the pot.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And the Germans-- of course, it was a German cookhouse, you know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Service cookhouse with very good equipment.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And the Germans I put on cleaning the place up, because there was excreta everywhere.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that's really how we got into the camp, and as I got around and saw the size of the camp and the problems we had-- because we had to escort the Germans, because prisoners were now taken it out on the Germans, but where we were putting Germans on cleaning up, the last thing we wanted them to be interfered with.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So go and take it out on some Germans somewhere else, and leave these alone.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They're doing the cleaning up job.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the Russians, I mean, the Russians were bloody terrible.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But you know, they'd been treated abominably.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But my colonel gave me free run.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I closed all the bakeries in the town for five days, and all the bread came into the camp.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then my colonel [INAUDIBLE] my colonel, and he said, I had to release some of it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he said, you needn't brother, Ted, I've already done it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So he released some for the townspeople.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then, of course, we had to register these people, and the way we did that was very simple.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
